{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.6",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 6 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:1",
      "text": "But Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:2",
      "text": "Oh that my grief were throughly weighed, and my calamity laid in the balances together!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:3",
      "text": "For now it would be heavier than the sand of the sea: therefore my words are swallowed up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:4",
      "text": "For the arrows of the Almighty are within me, the poison whereof drinketh up my spirit: the terrors of God do set themselves in array against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:5",
      "text": "Doth the wild ass bray when he hath grass? or loweth the ox over his fodder?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:6",
      "text": "Can that which is unsavoury be eaten without salt? or is there any taste in the white of an egg?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:7",
      "text": "The things that my soul refused to touch are as my sorrowful meat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:8",
      "text": "Oh that I might have my request; and that God would grant me the thing that I long for!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:9",
      "text": "Even that it would please God to destroy me; that he would let loose his hand, and cut me off!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:10",
      "text": "Then should I yet have comfort; yea, I would harden myself in sorrow: let him not spare; for I have not concealed the words of the Holy One.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:11",
      "text": "What is my strength, that I should hope? and what is mine end, that I should prolong my life?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:12",
      "text": "Is my strength the strength of stones? or is my flesh of brass?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:13",
      "text": "Is not my help in me? and is wisdom driven quite from me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:14",
      "text": "To him that is afflicted pity should be shewed from his friend; but he forsaketh the fear of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:15",
      "text": "My brethren have dealt deceitfully as a brook, and as the stream of brooks they pass away;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:16",
      "text": "Which are blackish by reason of the ice, and wherein the snow is hid:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:17",
      "text": "What time they wax warm, they vanish: when it is hot, they are consumed out of their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:18",
      "text": "The paths of their way are turned aside; they go to nothing, and perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:19",
      "text": "The troops of Tema looked, the companies of Sheba waited for them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:20",
      "text": "They were confounded because they had hoped; they came thither, and were ashamed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:21",
      "text": "For now ye are nothing; ye see my casting down, and are afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:22",
      "text": "Did I say, Bring unto me? or, Give a reward for me of your substance?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:23",
      "text": "Or, Deliver me from the enemy’s hand? or, Redeem me from the hand of the mighty?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:24",
      "text": "Teach me, and I will hold my tongue: and cause me to understand wherein I have erred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:25",
      "text": "How forcible are right words! but what doth your arguing reprove?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:26",
      "text": "Do ye imagine to reprove words, and the speeches of one that is desperate, which are as wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:27",
      "text": "Yea, ye overwhelm the fatherless, and ye dig a pit for your friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:28",
      "text": "Now therefore be content, look upon me; for it is evident unto you if I lie.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:29",
      "text": "Return, I pray you, let it not be iniquity; yea, return again, my righteousness is in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.6.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:30",
      "text": "Is there iniquity in my tongue? cannot my taste discern perverse things?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
